it seems that a mob designed to require sanctification to tank could just as easily be tanked by twice as many warriors, couldn't it?  After all, the paladin discipline would keep him alive for ONE instance of the huge damage proc/harmtouch/whatever, but ONLY if he timed it correctly, and the second instance would kill the paladin in question, since Sanc wouldn't have refreshed yet.<br>
<br>
You could just as easily do that with twice as many warriors, I would think, and you wouldn't have to worry about the paladins timing their disciplines properly.  Furthermore, warriors are probably easier to come up with in end game raids than fully equipped paladins.  Or am I wrong about that (I honestly don't know)?<br>
<br>
I think the best mob type that a paladin could MT would have to be something that required paladin spells to maintain aggro.  An undead mob that is just as powerful as any other end game mob, but which has real aggro problems, such that the main tank has to WORK HARD to keep aggro.  A paladin with Combat Fury 3, Slay undead 3, Instrument of Nife, and Dawncaller or Great Spear of Dawn should be able to keep aggro fairly easily, as long as he tossed in some Flash of Light, cease, desist, etc.<br>
<br>
Against an undead mob like that, I really don't think a warrior could main tank as effectively as a paladin, although it would certainly require more complete heals on the paladin than it would if the Main Tank were a warrior.<br>
<br>
Kether said it best when he said something like:  The most efficient way to do an encounter is going to be the most efficient way to do an encounter, even if that means having a paladin as main tank.  (sorry for the paraphrase, Kether)<br>
<br>
I would rate &quot;least amount of dead bodies after a battle&quot; as the &quot;most efficient way to do an encounter.&quot;  And if that means having a third more clerics or even 50% more clerics along, just to heal one paladin, I'd call that worth it if no one died. <p>Aragir Lancot<BR>
"One man plus the truth equals a majority."<BR>
<BR>
Paladin of the 48th shield<BR>
